2. Map of Mindanao per Region

# Region
ph_region <- gadm(country = "PHL", level = 1, path = tempdir())
ph_region_sf <- st_as_sf(ph_region)

# List of Mindanao provinces
mindanao_provinces <- c(
  # Zamboanga Peninsula 3
  "Zamboanga del Norte", "Zamboanga del Sur", "Zamboanga Sibugay",
  # Northern Mindanao 5
  "Bukidnon", "Camiguin", "Lanao del Norte", "Misamis Occidental", "Misamis Oriental",
  # Davao Region 5
  "Compostela Valley", "Davao del Norte", "Davao del Sur", "Davao Oriental", "Davao Occidental",
  # SOCCSKSARGEN 4
  "North Cotabato", "Sarangani", "South Cotabato", "Sultan Kudarat",
  # Caraga 5
  "Agusan del Norte", "Agusan del Sur", "Surigao del Norte", "Surigao del Sur", "Dinagat Islands",
  # BARMM 5
  "Lanao del Sur", "Maguindanao", "Basilan", "Sulu", "Tawi-Tawi"
)

# Filter Mindanao provinces
mindanao_sf <- ph_region_sf %>%
  filter(NAME_1 %in% mindanao_provinces)

# custom by region
mindanao_sf <- mindanao_sf %>%
  mutate(region = case_when(
    NAME_1 %in% c("Zamboanga del Norte", "Zamboanga del Sur", "Zamboanga Sibugay") ~ "Region IX – Zamboanga Peninsula",
    NAME_1 %in% c("Bukidnon", "Camiguin", "Lanao del Norte", "Misamis Occidental", "Misamis Oriental") ~ "Region X – Northern Mindanao",
    NAME_1 %in% c("Compostela Valley", "Davao del Norte", "Davao del Sur", "Davao Occidental", "Davao Oriental") ~ "Region XI – Davao Region",
    NAME_1 %in% c("Sultan Kudarat", "North Cotabato", "Sarangani", "South Cotabato") ~ "Region XII – SOCCSKSARGEN",
    NAME_1 %in% c("Agusan del Norte", "Agusan del Sur", "Surigao del Norte", "Surigao del Sur", "Dinagat Islands") ~ "Region XIII – Caraga",
    NAME_1 %in% c("Maguindanao","Basilan", "Lanao del Sur", "Sulu", "Tawi-Tawi") ~ "BARMM – Bangsamoro",
    TRUE ~ "Other"
  ))

# Define region-level colors
region_colors <- c(
  "Region IX – Zamboanga Peninsula" = "palegreen",
  "Region X – Northern Mindanao"    = "lightyellow",
  "Region XI – Davao Region"        = "lightblue",
  "Region XII – SOCCSKSARGEN"       = "orange",
  "Region XIII – Caraga"            = "lavender",
  "BARMM – Bangsamoro"              = "pink"
)

# Plot with ggplot
ggplot(mindanao_sf) +
  geom_sf(aes(fill = region), color = "black", size = 0.2) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = region_colors, name = "") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(legend.position = "right") +
  labs(title = "Map of Mindanao")

dengue_Mindanao.xlsx is already cleaned from the original data provided by the Department of Health (DOH). You can access it using this link: https://tinyurl.com/2s4mytuu.

4. Data Cleaning

Remove NA values from the data

dengue_clean <- dengue_raw %>%
  filter(!is.na(Cases))

5. Summary of Dengue Cases

Extract year, province, muncity and sum of Dengue cases

cases_summary <- dengue_clean %>%
  group_by(Year, Region, Province, Muncity) %>%
  summarise(cases = sum(Cases), .groups = "drop")

A total of 501,229 Dengue cases were recorded in Mindanao for the years 2017 to 2025

sum(cases_summary$cases)
## [1] 501229

Descriptive Statistics of accumulated number of Dengue cases per year (2017-2025)

Descriptive Statistics of weekly counts per Municipality

weekly_summary <- dengue_clean %>%
  group_by(Province, Muncity) %>%
  summarise(
    mean_ = sprintf("%.2f", mean(Cases)),
    med_  = sprintf("%.2f", median(Cases)),
    var_ = sprintf("%.2f", var(Cases)),
    sd_   = sprintf("%.2f", sd(Cases)),
    min_  = min(Cases),
    max_  = max(Cases),
    .groups = "drop"
  ) %>%
  arrange(desc(max_))   # sort from highest to lowest max cases

6. Trends of Weekly Dengue Cases from 2017-2025

df_summary <- dengue_clean %>%
  group_by(Year, `Morbidity Week`) %>%
  summarise(total_cases = sum(Cases), .groups = "drop")
# Line plot
ggplot(df_summary, aes(x = `Morbidity Week`, y = total_cases, color = factor(Year))) +
  geom_line(size = 1) +
  labs(
    title = "Average Weekly Case Counts by Year",
    x = "Week of Year",
    y = "Total Cases",
    color = "Year"
  ) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = 1:52) +   # show all weeks 1–52
  theme_minimal()

7. Map Dengue Cases per Region per Year

# Aggregate by year
cases_year <- dengue_clean %>%
  group_by(Year, Province) %>%
  summarise(cases = sum(Cases), .groups = "drop")

# Filter Mindanao provinces
mindanao_sf <- ph_region_sf %>%
  filter(NAME_1 %in% mindanao_provinces)

# Join dengue cases with polygons
mindanao_cases <- mindanao_sf %>%
  left_join(cases_year,
            by = c("NAME_1" = "Province")) %>%
  filter(!is.na(Year))   #drop any NA years here too

# modified color
mindanao_cases <- mindanao_cases %>%
  mutate(
    incidence_cat = cut(
      cases,
      breaks = c(-Inf, 45, 178, 618, 1000, Inf),
      labels = c("<45", "45–178", "179–618", "619–1000", ">10001"),
      right = TRUE
    )
  )

#Choropleth per year (faceted)
ggplot(mindanao_cases) +
  geom_sf(aes(fill = incidence_cat), color = "black", size = 0.2) +
  scale_fill_manual(
    values = c(
      "<45" = "lightblue",
      "45–178" = "lightgreen",
      "179–618" = "yellow",
      "619–1000" = "orange",
      ">10001" = "red"
    )
  ) +
  facet_wrap(~ Year) +
  labs(
    title = "",
    fill = "Total cases"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()

Municipalities: Map of Incidence Ratio (IR) for 10,000 population for Dengue Cases

# Compute the  incidence rates using 2020 population
dengue_clean$rate <- with(dengue_clean, Cases/Population2020*10^5)

# Aggregate by year
incidence_rate <- dengue_clean %>%
  group_by(Year, Province, Muncity) %>%
  summarise(cases = sum(rate), .groups = "drop")

# municipalities (admin level 2)
ph_muni <- gadm(country = "PHL", level = 2, path = tempdir())
ph_muni_sf <- st_as_sf(ph_muni)

# Filter Mindanao municipalities
incidence_muni <- ph_muni_sf %>%
  filter(NAME_1 %in% mindanao_provinces)

# Join dengue cases with polygons
incidence_cases <- incidence_muni %>%
  left_join(incidence_rate,
            by = c("NAME_1" = "Province",
                   "NAME_2" = "Muncity")) %>%
  filter(!is.na(Year))   #drop any NA years here too

# modified color
incidence_cases <- incidence_cases %>%
  mutate(
    incidence_cat = cut(
      cases,
      breaks = c(-Inf, 45, 90, 135, 178, Inf),
      labels = c("<45", "45–90", "91–135", "136–178", ">178"),
      right = TRUE
    )
  )

#Choropleth per year (faceted)
ggplot(incidence_cases) +
  geom_sf(aes(fill = incidence_cat), color = "black", size = 0.2) +
  scale_fill_manual(
    values = c(
      "<45" = "lightblue",
      "45–90" = "lightgreen",
      "91–135" = "yellow",
      "136–178" = "orange",
      ">178" = "red"
    )
  ) +
  facet_wrap(~ Year) +
  labs(
    title = "Incidence Ratio per 10,000 population",
    fill = ""
  ) +
  theme_minimal()
